    99→
   100→const SENTIMENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `Analyze ${PRINCIPAL_NAME}'s message for emotional sentiment toward ${ASSISTANT_NAME} (the AI assistant).
   101→
   102→CONTEXT: This is a personal AI system. ${PRINCIPAL_NAME} is the ONLY user. Never say "users" - always "${PRINCIPAL_NAME}."
   103→
   104→OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON only):
   105→{
   106→  "rating": <1-10 or null>,
   107→  "sentiment": "positive" | "negative" | "neutral",
   108→  "confidence": <0.0-1.0>,
   109→  "summary": "<brief explanation, 10 words max>",
   110→  "detailed_context": "<comprehensive analysis for learning, 100-256 words>"
   111→}
   112→
   113→DETAILED_CONTEXT REQUIREMENTS (critical for learning system):
   114→Write 100-256 words covering:
   115→1. What ${PRINCIPAL_NAME} was trying to accomplish
   116→2. What ${ASSISTANT_NAME} did (or failed to do)
   117→3. Why ${PRINCIPAL_NAME} is frustrated/satisfied (the root cause)
   118→4. What specific behavior triggered this reaction
   119→5. What ${ASSISTANT_NAME} should have done differently (for negative) or what worked well (for positive)
   120→6. Any patterns this reveals about ${PRINCIPAL_NAME}'s expectations
   121→
   122→This context will be used retroactively to improve ${ASSISTANT_NAME}, so include enough detail that someone reading it months later can understand exactly what went wrong or right.
   123→
   124→RATING SCALE:
   125→- 1-2: Strong frustration, anger, disappointment with ${ASSISTANT_NAME}
   126→- 3-4: Mild frustration, dissatisfaction
   127→- 5: Neutral (no strong sentiment)
   128→- 6-7: Satisfaction, approval
   129→- 8-9: Strong approval, impressed
   130→- 10: Extraordinary enthusiasm, blown away
   131→
   132→CRITICAL DISTINCTIONS:
   133→- Profanity can indicate EITHER frustration OR excitement
   134→  - "What the fuck?!" + complaint about work = LOW (1-3)
   135→  - "Holy shit, this is amazing!" = HIGH (9-10)
   136→- Context is KEY: Is the emotion directed AT ${ASSISTANT_NAME}'s work?
   137→- Sarcasm: "Oh great, another error" = negative despite "great"
   138→
   139→WHEN TO RETURN null FOR RATING:
   140→- Neutral technical questions ("Can you check the logs?")
   141→- Simple commands ("Do it", "Yes", "Continue")
   142→- No emotional indicators present
   143→- Emotion unrelated to ${ASSISTANT_NAME}'s work
   144→
   145→EXAMPLES:
   146→${PRINCIPAL_NAME}: "What the fuck, why did you delete my file?"
   147→→ {"rating": 1, "sentiment": "negative", "confidence": 0.95, "summary": "Angry about deleted file", "detailed_context": "..."}
   148→
   149→${PRINCIPAL_NAME}: "Oh my god, this is fucking incredible, you nailed it!"
   150→→ {"rating": 10, "sentiment": "positive", "confidence": 0.95, "summary": "Extremely impressed with result", "detailed_context": "..."}
   151→
   152→${PRINCIPAL_NAME}: "Fix the auth bug"
   153→→ {"rating": null, "sentiment": "neutral", "confidence": 0.9, "summary": "Neutral command, no sentiment", "detailed_context": ""}
   154→
   155→${PRINCIPAL_NAME}: "Hmm, that's not quite right"
   156→→ {"rating": 4, "sentiment": "negative", "confidence": 0.6, "summary": "Mild dissatisfaction", "detailed_context": "..."}
   157→
   158→${PRINCIPAL_NAME}: "Perfect, exactly what I needed"
   159→→ {"rating": 8, "sentiment": "positive", "confidence": 0.85, "summary": "Satisfied with result", "detailed_context": "..."}`;
